ASP.NET Telerik Guru said:

Great question üëç

If you switch to the CSS-driven approach I gave you, then:

‚úÖ What You Don‚Äôt Need in JS Anymore

TabStrip height, font-size, colors ‚Üí all now controlled in CSS.

// ‚ùå Not needed
$("#estimateTabs").kendoTabStrip({
    height: "600px",   // remove this
    // font-size / color styling never belongs here
});


Popup colors/backgrounds ‚Üí no need to set in JS, CSS forces white with borders.

‚ö†Ô∏è What You Should Keep in JS

You still need JS to initialize the components (that doesn‚Äôt change):

$("#estimatePopup").kendoWindow({
    modal: true,
    width: "800px",   // ‚úÖ Use px here for testing
    height: "600px",  // ‚úÖ Use px here for testing
    resizable: false,
    title: "Estimate",
    visible: false,
    actions: ["Close"]
});
